40-1308. POWER TO LEVY TAXES FOR COMPREHENSIVE INSURANCE, PROSECUTING AND DEFENDING ACTIONS, JUDGMENTS AND LIABILITIES. Every highway district has the power to levy and collect taxes as necessary to:

(1) Pay for a comprehensive insurance plan as provided in section 6-927, Idaho Code;

(2) Defray all expenses of prosecuting and defending actions;

(3) Pay any judgments and liabilities incurred against it; and

(4) Pay for emergencies or calamities as provided in section 40-820, Idaho Code.

[40-1308, added 1985, ch. 253, sec. 2, p. 649; am. 1999, ch. 332, sec. 6, p. 901; am. 2003, ch. 68, sec. 2, p. 229.]
